  "text": "The significant increase in reticulocyte count with iron isomaltoside 1000 vs. placebo at day 5 shows that the erythropoietic effect of iron isomaltoside 1000 has a rapid onset. Our results on Hb were in line with a previous trial where oral iron supplementation as a four-week course of ferrous sulphate prior to surgery in patients undergoing total hip or knee replacement protected the patients against a fall in Hb during the immediate postoperative period [14] . On the other hand, oral iron did not increase preoperative Hb in patients scheduled for hip or knee arthroplasty [CITATION_1] and often a 4-week preoperative course is not achievable or tolerated in surgery patients. In another trial, preoperative IV iron administration in anaemic patients undergoing major elective surgery also resulted in significant increase in Hb levels and a high rate of anaemia correction [15] .",
